description:
Supplemental Fig. 1 The phenotypes of embryos injected with different concentration of  duox  morpholino.    The   survival rate (A); hatch rate (B); malformation rate (C); (D-E)  tsh  and  tg  mRNA expression at 5 dpf by Q-PCR. SD, embryos injected with standard control morpholino. MO, embryos injected with  duox  morpholino. *, P&lt;0.05; **, P&lt;0.01; ***,  P  &lt; 0.001, compared with SD. 

 &nbsp; 

  Supplemental Fig. 2 The phenotypes of morphants treated with different concentration of T4 (5 nM, 10 nM, 50 nM, 100 nM) from 10 hpf.  (A), Heart rate; (B), Body length; (C), Eye size; (D), Ear size; (E-F),  tg  and  tsh  mRNA expression at 5 dpf by Q-PCR. SD, embryos injected with standard control morpholino. MO, embryos injected with  duox  morpholino. *, P&lt;0.05; **, P&lt;0.01; ***,  P  &lt; 0.001, compared with SD. 

 &nbsp; 

  Supplemental Fig. 3 The body length of  duox  KO mutants and wildtype from birth to juvenile.  No apparent growth defect was detected in larvae between two groups at the earlier age before 20 dpf, after 20 dpf,  duox  KO mutants were significantly shorter than wildtype. **, P&lt;0.01.

